<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
    <meta name="description" content="Simple project cost calculator">
    <meta name="author" content="Sergio Duran">

    <title>Simple Cost Calculator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-MCw98/SFnGE8fJT3GXwEOngsV7Zt27NXFoaoApmYm81iuXoPkFOJwJ8ERdknLPMO" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/pretty-print-json@0.0/dist/pretty-print-json.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/bs-callouts.css">

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.min.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.14.3/umd/popper.min.js" integrity="sha384-ZMP7rVo3mIykV+2+9J3UJ46jBk0WLaUAdn689aCwoqbBJiSnjAK/l8WvCWPIPm49" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-ChfqqxuZUCnJSK3+MXmPNIyE6ZbWh2IMqE241rYiqJxyMiZ6OW/JmZQ5stwEULTy" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/pretty-print-json@0.0/dist/pretty-print-json.min.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
      <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm">
                  <h1>Simple cost calculator</h1>
                  This app can calculate the costs for a project, how many products you can make, and how many resources you need to buy. It can automatically fill in the amounts if needed.<br>
                  For example, you can use it to calculate:<br>
                  <ul>
                      <li>How much it would cost to <a href="#" onclick="return loadJSON('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sheco/cocain/master/samples/chocomilk.json')">make 60 glasses of chocolate milk</a>, and how much milk and chocolate you would need.</li>
                      <li>How much it would cost to <a href="#" onclick="return loadJSON('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sheco/cocain/master/samples/chocomilk5liters.json')">make as many glasses of chocolate milk as possible, using only 5 liters of milk</a>, and how much chocolate you need.</li>
                 </ul>
                  <p>
                    You need to use valid JSON code, the syntax is simple but writing it can be a little daunting at first, you can use a JSON linter to validate the code,
                    for example: <a href="https://jsonlint.com/" target="_blank">https://jsonlint.com/</a>
                  </p>

              </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card-deck mb-2">
              <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
                  <div class="card-header">
                      Enter the JSON code
                  </div>
                  <div class="card-body">

                      <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-primary">
                      <form>
                          <div class="form-group">
                              <textarea name="src" id="src" class="form-control" rows="15" cols="40">{{src}}</textarea>
                          </div>
                          <button class="btn btn-block btn-primary" onclick="return calculate()">Calculate</button>
                      </form>

                      <br>
                      </div>

                      <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-success">
                      <form method="post" action="/convertCsv" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                          <div class="form-group">
                              <label for="csv">Convert a CSV file into JSON</label>
                              <input class="form-control-file" type="file" name="csv" id="csv" aria-describedby="csvHelp">
                          </div>

                          <small class="form-text text-muted" id="csvHelp">
                              This way you can upload a simple CSV and have it
                              converted to JSON and then calculated.
                              <br>
                              You can use the 
                              <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/Sheco/cocain/blob/master/samples/chocomilk.csv">sample CSV</a>
                              for reference, or check the documentation
                              in the project's github page.
                          </small>
                          <button class="btn btn-block btn-outline-success" onclick="return convertCsv()">Convert and calculate</button>
                      </form>
                      </div>
                   </div>
              </div>

              <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
                  <div class="card-header">
                      Result
                  </div>

                  <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="progress" id="progress" style="display: none">
                            <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped progress-bar-animated" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 100%"></div>
                        </div>
                        <pre id="result"></pre>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm">
                  <p>
                      Load JSON from one of the predefined samples, from <a href="https://github.com/Sheco/cocain/tree/master/samples">https://github.com/Sheco/cocain/tree/master/samples</a>, it's worth mentioning that the prices there are in Mexican pesos.
                      <ul id="samples"></ul>
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    The source code is available at <a href="https://github.com/Sheco/cocain">https://github.com/Sheco/cocain</a>
                    There you will find this app's documentation.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Written by Sergio Duran.
                  <p>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
    <script>
        function calculate() {
            $("#progress").show()
            document.getElementById("progress").scrollIntoView()

            $.post('/api', {
                src: $("#src").val()
            }, function(data) {
                $("#result").html(prettyPrintJson.toHtml(data))
                $("#progress").hide()

                // flash the result pane
                $("#result").fadeIn(100).fadeOut(100).fadeIn(100).fadeOut(100).fadeIn(100);
            }, "json")

            return false
        }

        function loadJSON(url) {
            $.get(url, function(json) {
                $("#src").val(json)
                calculate()
            });
            return false;
        }

        function convertCsv() {
            $("#result").html('Loading...')

            let formData = new FormData()
            formData.append('csv', $("#csv").get(0).files[0])
            
            $.ajax({               
                url: '/convertCsv',
                data: formData,
                processData: false,
                contentType: false,
                type: 'POST',
                success: function( data ){
                    $("#src").val(data)
                    calculate()
                }
            });      
            return false;
        }

        $(function() {
            let root = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sheco/cocain/master/samples/'
            let samples = {
                'Bibs': root+'bibs.json',
                'Chocomilk': root+'chocomilk.json',
                'Stickers': root+'stickers.json',
                'Chocoavena': root+'chocoavena.json',
                'Fabric Tree': root+'tree.json'
            };

            let samples_ul = $("#samples");
            for (let [name, url] of Object.entries(samples)) {
                samples_ul.append($(`<li><a href="${url}" onclick="return loadJSON('${url}')">${name}</a></li>`));
            }
        });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
